abstract: The Times sent a survey to the 2020 candidates about their understanding of the scope and limits of the presidential authority they would wield if elected.

abstract: The companies seem to have fallen short in efforts to dodge legislation classifying many workers in the gig economy as employees and not contractors.
snippet: The companies seem to have fallen short in efforts to dodge legislation classifying many workers in the gig economy as employees and not contractors.
lead_paragraph: SACRAMENTO  A pack of Teamsters fanned out through Californias Capitol building last week, marching into legislators offices and pressing them to pass a bill that would force Uber and Lyft to treat their drivers as employees. The measure, Assembly Bill 5, would entitle gig workers to protections like a minimum wage and unemployment benefits. Yes on A.B. 5! Yes on A.B. 5! they chorused.

abstract: The Vermont senator has staked his presidential campaign, and much of his political legacy, on transforming health care in America. His mothers illness, and a trip he made to study the Canadian system, help explain why.
snippet: The Vermont senator has staked his presidential campaign, and much of his political legacy, on transforming health care in America. His mothers illness, and a trip he made to study the Canadian system, help explain why.
lead_paragraph: BURLINGTON, Vt.  In July 1987, Bernie Sanders, then the mayor of Burlington, Vt., arrived in Ottawa convinced he was about to see the future of health care.

abstract: In an interview, Ms. Harris sought to paint her prosecutorial career as a reason voters should rely on her to deliver a criminal justice overhaul. But her critics say she has been part of the problem.
snippet: In an interview, Ms. Harris sought to paint her prosecutorial career as a reason voters should rely on her to deliver a criminal justice overhaul. But her critics say she has been part of the problem.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California released a sweeping proposal on Monday to overhaul the criminal justice system, vowing to end mass incarceration and revamp police practices through a progressive wish list of policies, including some ideas Ms. Harris previously rejected during her years as a district attorney and state attorney general.
